 background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_02.gif"><span CLASS="newsdate">Sun 11 May 2008</span></TD><TD><IMG SRC="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_03.gif"></TD></TR></TABLE><br><!-------Start News item--><table cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="94%" border=0>             <tr>           <td width=23><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_01.jpg"></td>           <td  width=100%        background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_02.jpg"></td>           <td><img         src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_03.jpg"></td></tr>         <tr>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_04.jpg" width="17px">&nbsp;</td>           <td             background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_05.jpg" class="newsbody"><a name="41150"></a><span CLASS="newstitle"><a href="/fullstory.php?id=41150">Video Contest Special Shout Out</a> &nbsp;<span class="newscomments">[ <a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/forums/b1/107298658">Comment <img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/global/commenticon.gif" border="0"></a> ]</span></span><br><span class="feat"><a href=pagetools/pagetools.php?act=printnews&id=41150>Print News</a> | Category: <a href="/?category_id=17">Community News</a></span><br><span class="newsbody">Congrats to all the winners of the <a href="http://eqplayers.station.sony.com/news_article.vm?id=50924">SOE video contest,</a> but a special shout out from Kwill goes to third place winner Grumpie, who is in my very own guild!<br><br>Apparently Grumpie earned the healing from all those CH chains I participated in so he could live to make the great movie that earned him a prize in the "You're In Our World Now" video contest.<br><br>I love seeing videos of all my friends in Crimson Talon, many of whom I have known for many years now.  We are one of the oldest guilds on the Cazic Thule server.  Grats Grumpie on a great job with the camera work and the music!<br><br>Grumpie Ogarfiend<br>Server:  Cazic-Thule<br>Guild:  Crimson Talon<br><br>The Traveling Ogre<br>This little memento was produced Ogarfiend's Gnomalicious Production House in the span of four and a half hours. It's a snapshot of life in our guild named the Crimson Talon which plays on the Cazic Thule server. It's about how we come together to help each other out and enjoy EverQuest. It features a nice horse ride through what would seem ominous territory, but then the dangers looming ahead become very clear and visible. Follow the journey of an Ogre traversing the maze to help his fellow cleric finish an epic fight then be transported ahead to another plane of existence to meet up with the Fabled Lord Mithaniel Marr in a harrowing display of his arrogance. (music files used were Anguish, blackfeaatherroost, poffire, and thenest.mp3)<br><br>Grats also to these talented film makers:<br><br>Second Place Winners:<br><br>Tnexus_Prexus <br>Character:  Tnexus the Forgotten Hero<br>Server:  Prexus<br>Guild:  Hand of Ka <br><br>Meekrat-cleric <br>Character:  Meekrat<br>Server:  Povar<br>Guild:  Firestormers <br><br>Sylvanias <br>Character:  Sylvanias Windrunner<br>Server:  saryrn<br>Guild:  Travelers of Norrath <br><br>Third Place Winners:<br> <br>Teannin <br>Character:  Teannin Pokes<br>Server:  Maelin Starpyre<br>Guild:  Crimson Tempest <br><br>Gelv <br>Character:  Gelvelik<br>Server:  Povar<br>Guild:  Firestormers <br>You're in our World - Come Together<br></span><br><br><span CLASS="newsby">-- <a href="/siteinfo/mail.php?staff=Kwill">Kwill</a> @ Sun 11 May 2008</span><br><br><br><a name="41141"></a><span CLASS="newstitle"><a href="/fullstory.php?id=41141">May Developer Chat This Week</a> &nbsp;<span class="newscomments">[ <a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/forums/b1/107294534">Comment <img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/global/commenticon.gif" border="0"></a> ]</span></span><br><span class="feat"><a href=pagetools/pagetools.php?act=printnews&id=41141>Print News</a> | Category: <a href="/?category_id=17">Community News</a></span><br><span class="newsbody">From <a href="http://mmorpg.com/discussion2.cfm?THREAD=177625&bhcp=1">MMORPG.com:</a><br><br>Come meet Ryan "Rytan" Barker, the new lead designer for SOE's EverQuest, live in the MMORPG.com Chatroom!<br><br>Starting at 7pm EST on 05/13/08, the EverQuest developers will answer your questions about the game, world, recent updates, future plans, and the team direction under new lead designer Rytan! Bring a question, bring a friend! After the chat, be sure to stick around for EverQuest and other MMORPG discussion.<br><br>Users can connect via any IRC client, to server irc.coldfront.net port 6667. The chat will take place in #mmorpg.<br></span><br><br><span CLASS="newsby">-- <a href="/siteinfo/mail.php?staff=Kwill">Kwill</a> @ Sun 11 May 2008</span><br><br><br><a name="41140"></a><span CLASS="newstitle"><a href="/fullstory.php?id=41140">Winners of the SOE Video Contest</a> &nbsp;<span class="newscomments">[ <a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/forums/b1/107294194">Comment <img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/global/commenticon.gif" border="0"></a> ]</span></span><br><span class="feat"><a href=pagetools/pagetools.php?act=printnews&id=41140>Print News</a> | Category: <a href="/?category_id=16">EQ Live</a></span><br><span class="newsbody">Congratulations to Oriaas Farslayer from the The Tribunal server!<br><br><a href="http://eqplayers.station.sony.com/news_article.vm?id=50924">Brotherhood</a><br>Friendships built in game often last a long time. I am still friends with people that I played EQ with years ago - even tough they have moved on to other things. You never know where your next friend may come from which is probably one of the things I like best about EQ. You never know who you will meet and you never know if you will still interact with them several years down the line. <br><br>While there are many aspects to the game, it seems that many people often forget that it is still a game. That means you need to stop and take a look around sometime and see what you've been missing. </span><br><br><span CLASS="newsby">-- <a href="/siteinfo/mail.php?staff=Kwill">Kwill</a> @ Sun 11 May 2008</span><br><br><br><a name="41139"></a><span CLASS="newstitle"><a href="/fullstory.php?id=41139">Interview with Smedley</a> &nbsp;<span class="newscomments">[ <a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/forums/b1/107294169">Comment <img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/global/commenticon.gif" border="0"></a> ]</span></span><br><span class="feat"><a href=pagetools/pagetools.php?act=printnews&id=41139>Print News</a> | Category: <a href="/?category_id=16">EQ Live</a></span><br><span class="newsbody">Gamebiz.com has published an <a href="http://www.gamesindustry.biz/articles/mmo-week-soe-president-john-smedley">interview</a> with John Smedley, President of SOE.<br><br>Looks like SOE is concentrating on some of their new titles which include Real Money Transactions (RMT) such as Free Realms, but aren't forgetting the lessons learned on how to run an MMO, most importantly listening to their customers (and the most annoyed ones, at that).<br><br>Here is a snippet of their conversation that particularly pertains to SOE's MMO titles:<br><br>Q: Looking back, SOE has been a big cog in the MMO market over time - how important has the portfolio plan been to you? <br><br>John Smedley: Yeah, that was something that we focused on pretty early, and we've had pretty much a success in it. We tried some things - we were the first people out there with an MMOFPS - and with that we're going to do it again, we've just got to learn the lessons. <br><br>We're on generation two, whereas everybody else is on generation one - and I think that will give us a leg-up in our future titles. <br><br>Q: What have you learned about the community aspect - Star Wars: Galaxies, for example, went through a difficult transition period. <br><br>John Smedley: The lessons we've learned from our community have just been extraordinary. For years now we've been running something called the Influencer Summit, where we pull 100 people, and 50 of those people will be our worst critics. <br><br>So one of the things we're trying to do is listen better as a company, and over the past few years I think we've done that - I'm really proud of the strides we've taken in that direction. Listening is a very important skill. <br><br>Q: Why do you think there was that response? <br><br>John Smedley: Because we didn't listen. I think we were a little too arrogant as a company. We thought we knew what was best as a company, and we should have listened more. That's really the biggest lesson we've learned as a company in the last eight years. Listening to our customers is everything. <br><br>Q: Does that influence strategy as far as beta-tests go, when you're looking to get feedback around the games? <br><br>John Smedley: It does, because we now have a much better mechanism in place for listening to customer feedback. Our entire company is very quality-oriented now, and extremely focused around making sure that we're giving the users, who are paying the bills, something that they want, and that's fun. <br><br>And a direct quote on micro-transactions:<br><br>"John Smedley: We're a big believer in micro-transactions, we certainly think they are part of the future, and that's why we invested in the collectible card business, because we wanted to be in micro-transactions early in the US, and it's been very successful. <br><br>I think it's a way to earn money that doesn't piss customers off, because if it gives them the opportunity to play something for free, and then they can just pay small amounts for clothing or whatever, I think that could really expand our space in a big way."<br><br>So there you have it -- look for more RMT and micro-transactions coming your way from SOE.  Whether or not they show up any more than they have in EQ or EQ2 will be the question, of course, but clearly the President of the company thinks it's a very good way to make money.</span><p><a href="fullstory.php?id=41139">Read More...</a><br><br><span CLASS="newsby">-- <a href="/siteinfo/mail.php?staff=Kwill">Kwill</a> @ Sun 11 May 2008</span><br><br><br><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/spacer.gif" width="540px" height=1></td>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_06.jpg" width="17px">&nbsp;</td></tr>         <tr>           <td width=23><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_07.jpg"></td>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_08.jpg"></td>           <td><img         src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_09.jpg"></td></tr></table></p><!-------End News item--><p><TABLE WIDTH="94%" BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0><TR><TD><IMG SRC="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_01.gif"></TD><TD WIDTH="100%" background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_02.gif"><span CLASS="newsdate">Fri 09 May 2008</span></TD><TD><IMG SRC="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_03.gif"></TD></TR></TABLE><br><!-------Start News item--><table cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="94%" border=0>             <tr>           <td width=23><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_01.jpg"></td>           <td  width=100%        background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_02.jpg"></td>           <td><img         src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_03.jpg"></td></tr>         <tr>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_04.jpg" width="17px">&nbsp;</td>           <td             background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_05.jpg" class="newsbody"><a name="41083"></a><span CLASS="newstitle"><a href="/fullstory.php?id=41083">Legends of Norrath Championship Qualifiers</a> &nbsp;<span class="newscomments">[ <a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/forums/b1/107273112">Comment <img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/global/commenticon.gif" border="0"></a> ]</span></span><br><span class="feat"><a href=pagetools/pagetools.php?act=printnews&id=41083>Print News</a> | Category: <a href="/?category_id=16">EQ Live</a></span><br><span class="newsbody">The Legends of Norrath Championship Tournament is just a few months away!  There's still time to qualify to play in Indianapolis starting August 16.<br><br>SOE has scheduled <a href="http://legendsofnorrath.station.sony.com/genCon.vm">Legends of Norrath</a> Championship Qualifier events to be held each month through July. These events should allow you to hone your skills against some of the best opponents available. $5,000 in prizes are set to be awarded for each event. Plus, if you win one of these events, you'll secure a spot in the World Championship Event scheduled to be held at <a href="http://www.gencon.com/2008/indy/">Gen Con Indy</a>, where you can compete for a share of the $100,000 prize pool.<br><br>Scheduled for May 17 - 18, 2008<br><br>Scheduled for June 14 - 15, 2008<br><br>Scheduled for July 12 - 13, 2008<br><br>Read more about all the events at GenCon below.<br></span><p><a href="fullstory.php?id=41083">Read More...</a><br><br><span CLASS="newsby">-- <a href="/siteinfo/mail.php?staff=Kwill">Kwill</a> @ Fri 09 May 2008</span><br><br><br><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/spacer.gif" width="540px" height=1></td>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_06.jpg" width="17px">&nbsp;</td></tr>         <tr>           <td width=23><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_07.jpg"></td>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_08.jpg"></td>           <td><img         src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_09.jpg"></td></tr></table></p><!-------End News item--><p><TABLE WIDTH="94%" BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0><TR><TD><IMG SRC="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_01.gif"></TD><TD WIDTH="100%" background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_02.gif"><span CLASS="newsdate">Wed 07 May 2008</span></TD><TD><IMG SRC="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_03.gif"></TD></TR></TABLE><br><!-------Start News item--><table cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="94%" border=0>             <tr>           <td width=23><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_01.jpg"></td>           <td  width=100%        background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_02.jpg"></td>           <td><img         src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_03.jpg"></td></tr>         <tr>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_04.jpg" width="17px">&nbsp;</td>           <td             background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_05.jpg" class="newsbody"><a name="41023"></a><span CLASS="newstitle"><a href="/fullstory.php?id=41023">New Tribute System Delayed</a> &nbsp;<span class="newscomments">[ <a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/forums/b1/107252618">Comment <img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/global/commenticon.gif" border="0"></a> ]</span></span><br><span class="feat"><a href=pagetools/pagetools.php?act=printnews&id=41023>Print News</a> | Category: <a href="/?category_id=16">EQ Live</a></span><br><span class="newsbody">The new tribute system was not included in this patch, and may not be pushed live for quite some time.  Ngreth <a href="http://forums.station.sony.com/eq/posts/list.m?start=45&topic_id=131942">posted</a>:<br><br>"Due to various oddities with the tribute system, this will not be going out until the expansion." <br><br>That would mean November, kiddies.</span><br><br><span CLASS="newsby">-- <a href="/siteinfo/mail.php?staff=Kwill">Kwill</a> @ Wed 07 May 2008</span><br><br><br><a name="41020"></a><span CLASS="newstitle"><a href="/fullstory.php?id=41020">Patch Notes May 7</a> &nbsp;<span class="newscomments">[ <a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/forums/b1/107252578">Comment <img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/global/commenticon.gif" border="0"></a> ]</span></span><br><span class="feat"><a href=pagetools/pagetools.php?act=printnews&id=41020>Print News</a> | Category: <a href="/?category_id=16">EQ Live</a></span><br><span class="newsbody">May 7, 2008<br>_____________________<br><br><br>*** Highlights ***<br><br>- Improvements have been made to the functionality of the EQPlayers pages.<br><br>- Secrets of Faydwer pet focus items have had their effects improved.<br></span><p><a href="fullstory.php?id=41020">Read More...</a><br><br><span CLASS="newsby">-- <a href="/siteinfo/mail.php?staff=Kwill">Kwill</a> @ Wed 07 May 2008</span><br><br><br><a name="41018"></a><span CLASS="newstitle"><a href="/fullstory.php?id=41018">Game Update</a> &nbsp;</span><br><span class="feat"><a href=pagetools/pagetools.php?act=printnews&id=41018>Print News</a> | Category: <a href="/?category_id=16">EQ Live</a></span><br><span class="newsbody">Game Update: All EverQuest Live Servers (except Al'Kabor) will be brought down at 5:00 am PDT on Wednesday, May 7, 2008 for a Game Update. The servers are estimated to be down for 6 hours. (PDT is -7 GMT: 6:00am MDT, 7:00am CDT, 8:00am EDT, 12:00 GMT). <br><br>SoF Evolving Items Reminder: With Wednesday's Game Update, we changed variations of the same Secrets of Faydwer evolving items that were not on lore groups to now share lore groups.<br><br>What this means is that if you somehow acquired two versions of the same Secrets of Faydwer evolving item, one of them will be removed after the patch due to the duplicate lore status. In order to select the version that you wish to keep, you should delete the version that you do not need. This change should only affect a minimal amount of people. <br></span><br><br><span CLASS="newsby">-- <a href="/siteinfo/mail.php?staff=Kwill">Kwill</a> @ Wed 07 May 2008</span><br><br><br><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/spacer.gif" width="540px" height=1></td>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_06.jpg" width="17px">&nbsp;</td></tr>         <tr>           <td width=23><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_07.jpg"></td>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_08.jpg"></td>           <td><img         src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_09.jpg"></td></tr></table></p><!-------End News item--></center>
